node.text: Yeah 👍 very convincing. the recognition of this particular use of the brain should be recognized, appreciated and remunerated like some people do math, economics or law. School of the sixth sense :-) to work in Sixth sense institue 🥰

Do we possess a sixth sense when it comes to creativity and the consumption of art?

We thought technology was going to open up new possibilities for human expression, giving us access to new information, new inspiration, and tools and techniques for creation. Join film director and digital artist Martha Fiennes, as she argues technology has all too often closed, not opened, our minds.

Tap the link in bio to watch this talk in full.

Yeah 👍 very convincing. the recognition of this particular use of the brain should be recognized, appreciated and remunerated like some people do math, economics or law. School of the sixth sense :-) to work in Sixth sense institue 🥰

All art is based on humanity. What it means to be human…

So why does art institutions make it so hard, to allow marginalised artists to thrive? When we are all human + have something to offer ❤️✨
Technology supports creativity, but it operates based on data and algorithms, lacking the spontaneous creativity that the human mind offers 🤷🏼‍♀️
Technology only works when it's open to change and modification🔥❤️❤️

caption.text:

Join film director and digital artist Martha Fiennes, as she argues technology has all too often closed, not opened, our minds.
